{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1002da48-d427-4414-bf93-e60f2cceaa8f","content":"Here's what to change:\n\n1. **Update NuGet packages:**\n   - Upgrade `NUnit3TestAdapter` to **v5.0.0+** (it bundles Microsoft.Testing.Platform support).\n   - Remove `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` — it's no longer needed.\n   - Add `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` if you need TRX output.\n\n2. **Set the test runner in your `.csproj`:**\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n3. **Run tests** the same way:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n\n**Key differences to be aware of:**\n- Each test project now produces its own executable (the test host).\n- CLI options change slightly (e.g., `--filter` becomes `--filter` on the new platform too, but some advanced VSTest `.runsettings` features may need adjustment).\n- Extensions (loggers, reporters) are now opted-in via NuGet packages rather than VSTest adapters.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"28112175-3b06-4890-aa42-ea7a91da2b76","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a general knowledge question - I don't need to search a codebase. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":340,"requestId":"A04A:262AAE:17E644A:1AF6E5E:69FE84FD"},"id":"82ed9934-504e-45ee-b312-3848e6932f67","timestamp":"2026-05-09T00:51:17.944Z","parentId":"f51e5059-c7fc-4072-98da-10b845e9b5bf"}
